Mirror a sketch.

Only works on unclosed sketches for now.
Mirror occurs around a local sketch axis rather than a global axis.

```js
mirror2d(data: Mirror2dData, sketch_group_set: SketchGroupSet) -> [SketchGroup]
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `data` | [`Mirror2dData`](kcl/types/Mirror2dData) | Data for a mirror. | Yes |
| `sketch_group_set` | [`SketchGroupSet`](kcl/types/SketchGroupSet) | A sketch group or a group of sketch groups. | Yes |

### Returns

[`[SketchGroup]`](kcl/types/[SketchGroup]) 


### Examples

```js
// Mirror an un-closed sketch across the Y axis.
const sketch001 = startSketchOn('XZ')
  |> startProfileAt([0, 10], %)
  |> line([15, 0], %)
  |> line([-7, -3], %)
  |> line([9, -1], %)
  |> line([-8, -5], %)
  |> line([9, -3], %)
  |> line([-8, -3], %)
  |> line([9, -1], %)
  |> line([-19, -0], %)
  |> mirror2d({ axis: 'Y' }, %)

const example = extrude(10, sketch001)
```
